# Agent Coordination Protocol

## Agent Roles & Priorities (from [docs/runbooks/AGENT_STATUS_MATRIX_2025-10-13T22-50.md](mdc:docs/runbooks/AGENT_STATUS_MATRIX_2025-10-13T22-50.md))

### P0 - Critical Path
- **Engineer**: Implementation, deployment, technical features
- **Deployment**: Production monitoring, health checks
- **QA**: Testing, validation, quality assurance

### P1 - High Priority
- **AI**: Knowledge base, LlamaIndex MCP, agent responses
- **Chatwoot**: CX integration, message handling
- **Data**: Database, analytics, RLS policies
- **Integrations**: Shopify, GA, external APIs

### P2 - Supporting
- **Designer**: UI/UX, specifications
- **Support**: Documentation, operator guides
- **Product**: Roadmap, launch materials
- **Marketing**: Campaigns, communications
- **Enablement**: Training, onboarding
- **Compliance**: Security, audits, policies
- **Reliability**: Monitoring, incident response
- **Git Cleanup**: Repository maintenance
- **Localization**: Content audit, voice/tone
- **Engineer Helper**: Code review, pairing
- **QA Helper**: Test coverage, quality

## Feedback Logging

**Required**: Log all progress to `feedback/{agent-name}.md`

**Format**:
```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ â€” Task Description

**Task**: Brief description
**Status**: Complete/In Progress/Blocked
**Duration**: Time taken

### Details
- Deliverable created
- Findings/results
- Evidence commands
- Next steps

**Next**: Next task
```

## Evidence Requirements
- Timestamp all actions (ISO 8601)
- Log commands executed
- Save artifacts to appropriate folders
- Reference file locations
- Document blockers explicitly

## Direction Files
Each agent has: `docs/directions/{agent-name}.md`
- Contains current priorities
- START HERE NOW section
- Canon/reference docs
- Task lists with estimates
